(r, \theta, z)
x = r \cos\theta
y= r\sin \theta
z=z
r
\theta
 x^2 + y^2 = (r\cos\theta)^2+(r\sin\theta)^2= r^2(\cos^2\theta+\sin^2\theta)= r^2 
 \cos\theta = \frac{x}{r} = \frac{x}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}
(\rho,\theta,\phi)
x = \rho\cos(\theta)\sin(\phi)
y= \rho\sin(\theta)\sin(\phi)
z = \rho \cos(\phi)
\rho,\theta
\phi
(r, \theta, z) = (\sqrt{2}, \pi/4, 1)
(\rho, \theta, \phi) = (\sqrt{3}, \pi/4, 0.955\text{ radians})
